@ontos 1.0
@title Open-source roadmap example
@type open-source-roadmap
@updated 2026-06-05

- Roadmap @id(roadmap) #roadmap #opensource
  status: active
  owner: maintainers
  purpose: Organize public work after the first stable release.
  current:
    - Protocol, parser, CLI, and examples form the initial foundation.
    - Viewer and editor integrations expand adoption.
  ai_task: Turn roadmap nodes into scoped issues.
  ai_boundary: Do not promise dates without maintainer approval.
  risk:
    - A broad roadmap may hide the most important compatibility work.
  verify:
    - Each roadmap item links to a release gate or user workflow.
    - Completed work has tests or documentation.
  history:
    - 2026-06-05 created official open-source roadmap example.

  - Tooling track @id(tooling-track) #tooling
    status: active
    depends_on: [[roadmap]]
    acceptance:
      - CLI supports validation, formatting, export, import, and packs.
      - Packages pass install and publish dry run checks.

    - Integration track @id(integration-track) #integrations
      purpose: Add editor and knowledge-tool integrations after core stability.
      verify:
        - Integration proposals reference stable protocol behavior.
